3
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:37,239
(Episode 36)

4
00:01:39,879 --> 00:01:40,959
Hou Jue.

5
00:01:43,959 --> 00:01:45,079
Tell me.

6
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:48,319
At what stage are you in your relationship with Shi Yi?

7
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,400
Don't even ask.

8
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,719
It was going pretty well before,

9
00:01:57,159 --> 00:01:59,280
but after you kept messing things up,

10
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:02,280
it has just become...

11
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:05,359
an innocent friendship.

12
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,760
What do you mean I messed things up?

13
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,439
You were the one who was indifferent to it.

14
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,560
Yes, I was indifferent.

15
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,840
But I used to have a house and a car.

16
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,479
I could take care of myself.

17
00:02:18,039 --> 00:02:22,280
Now, I'm managing a company on the brink of bankruptcy...

18
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:26,639
and my dad is sick.

19
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,840
Who on earth has the guts to be with me?

20
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:32,159
Listen to yourself.

21
00:02:33,439 --> 00:02:34,599
At first,

22
00:02:35,159 --> 00:02:37,530
I didn't think you have a prospect with Shi Yi.

23
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:39,879
But when I woke up this morning,

24
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:42,000
Shi Yi was standing next to you.

25
00:02:43,919 --> 00:02:45,120
For some reason,

26
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:47,960
I feel so reassured.

27
00:02:49,199 --> 00:02:50,280
If things...

28
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:52,919
are meant to work out between you and Shi Yi,

29
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,319
I couldn't be happier.

30
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:59,159
Then you two can have a child together.

31
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,400
I will step down...

32
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,919
and take care of my grandchild every day.

33
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,560
What do you think?

34
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,240
Hou Jue.

35
00:03:10,879 --> 00:03:11,960
Hou Jue.

36
00:03:16,199 --> 00:03:17,400
He's fast asleep.

37
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:27,360
I heard that your life was at stake.

38
00:03:35,039 --> 00:03:36,240
Yes.

39
00:03:36,919 --> 00:03:40,360
Maybe God wants me to live longer...

40
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,800
to pay for my sins.

41
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,719
I'm surprised.

42
00:03:48,479 --> 00:03:49,759
You, who are always right,

43
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:52,000
are talking about atonement.

44
00:04:00,759 --> 00:04:02,280
It's payback time.

45
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,120
I deserve it.

46
00:04:15,159 --> 00:04:16,439
In your heart,

47
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:19,050
I'm just a passerby.

48
00:04:20,439 --> 00:04:22,240
You don't care about me at all.

49
00:04:50,639 --> 00:04:52,639
Okay, I don't think I'm worth it.

50
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:00,800
I don't think I'm worth it.

51
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,800
Don't have lingering feelings for me.

52
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,439
The news that I had fallen sick...

53
00:05:20,730 --> 00:05:22,839
must have spread quickly in the industry.

54
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:25,319
It has been more than 10 hours,

55
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:30,120
but I didn't even receive a consoling call or text.

56
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,319
I've been forgotten by this world.

57
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,120
I've been abandoned.

58
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,360
You should forget about me too.

59
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:39,560
If I really forget you,

60
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:41,600
I won't contact you again.

61
00:05:42,439 --> 00:05:44,000
Do you know where I am?

62
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,040
I'm downstairs.

63
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,720
I don't have the courage to go up.

64
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,560
I don't even know which room you are in.

65
00:06:31,199 --> 00:06:33,040
Thank you for coming.

66
00:07:24,439 --> 00:07:25,800
I finally know...

67
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,639
the holy sense of taking care of someone.

68
00:07:29,079 --> 00:07:30,199
Of course it's hard.

69
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:33,800
I finally experience how you felt when you were beside me.

70
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,319
You have experienced so much,

71
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:37,000
but you didn't even say thank you.

72
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,920
A great favor can't be thanked enough with words.

73
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:14,839
Miss.

74
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,120
There's a patient named Hou Zhi Rong.

75
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,319
Which room is he in?

76
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:18,839
He's in room 510.

77
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,839
Room 510? Okay, thank you.

78
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,800
Give it to me.

79
00:08:28,639 --> 00:08:29,680
Wait outside.

80
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,519
He's asleep.

81
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:29,159
He's putting on quite an act.

82
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:36,360
Gosh! Were you pretending to be a corpse?

83
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,360
My goodness.

84
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:44,039
Are you really sick?

85
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:47,000
It looks like you're comfortable here.

86
00:09:47,450 --> 00:09:49,450
Why don't you try it?

87
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,279
Switch with me then.

88
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:53,919
Are you cursing me?

89
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,039
No way.

90
00:09:58,210 --> 00:10:00,360
But you are right.

91
00:10:00,679 --> 00:10:02,759
I didn't get enough sleep last night.

92
00:10:04,159 --> 00:10:06,799
I knew you didn't sleep well.

93
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:09,450
Really? You're very capable.

94
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,090
Of course. I can read your mind.

95
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:13,679
Keep going.

96
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,919
Guess why I couldn't sleep well.

97
00:10:19,879 --> 00:10:21,360
Why couldn't you sleep?

98
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:24,759
I want to hear it from you first. What is it?

99
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,480
I'm telling you.

100
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:30,960
It's family matter.

101
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,279
Family matter? No way.

102
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:38,240
Let me think. What is it?

103
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,720
Someone...

104
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:41,879
offended his best friend...

105
00:10:42,759 --> 00:10:46,159
because of something.

106
00:10:47,330 --> 00:10:48,919
As a result,

107
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:52,279
he doesn't find drinking fun anymore.

108
00:10:52,879 --> 00:10:54,639
Nobody talks to him either.

109
00:10:54,639 --> 00:10:55,679
Yes.

110
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:57,440
But he is too proud...

111
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,440
to apologize to his best friend.

112
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:02,120
That's why he's upset.

113
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,519
Just when he was clueless,

114
00:11:03,519 --> 00:11:05,679
an unexpected opportunity struck.

115
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:08,480
When I was predicting it,

116
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:11,440
I knew that even if he didn't come today,

117
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:14,279
he would be here tomorrow.

118
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,679
Isn't that you?

119
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:20,279
Mr. Sheng.

120
00:11:20,519 --> 00:11:21,559
Stop gloating.

121
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:23,519
You are so petty.

122
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,600
That's enough. Look at you.

123
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,720
You're a patient.

124
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:34,559
I'm here today to see you.

125
00:11:34,559 --> 00:11:35,600
So I won't argue with you.

126
00:11:36,039 --> 00:11:38,399
Fine. Do whatever you want.

127
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:41,080
I don't need your permission to do whatever I want.

128
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,559
I don't need you to compromise.

129
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,440
Zhi Rong.

130
00:11:50,039 --> 00:11:51,559
We have to talk about this.

131
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,639
I do dote on...

132
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,399
my daughter.

133
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,879
Those youngsters...

134
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:03,639
Sometimes, my daughter is indeed at fault.

135
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:07,279
I also did something that offended you.

136
00:12:08,759 --> 00:12:10,919
At least you know.

137
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,679
Speaking of our children,

138
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:16,320
you really do have a good son.

139
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,360
Of course.

140
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,519
Can you hand over your son?

141
00:12:20,759 --> 00:12:22,200
That's not a bad idea.

142
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,320
You didn't sleep...

143
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,799
for the whole night.

144
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,159
That's why you are daydreaming so early in the morning.

145
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,399
Dream on.

146
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:34,440
You have a daughter.

147
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,960
If I hand over my marvelous son to you,

148
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:38,000
you'll have both children.

149
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,000
What about me then?

150
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,480
I'll be alone forever.

151
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,960
I think heartless people like you...

152
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,559
should hand your daughter over to me...

153
00:12:44,919 --> 00:12:46,399
so that you'll be alone forever...

154
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:48,399
to repent and reflect upon yourself.

155
00:12:50,399 --> 00:12:52,519
But a cold-hearted person like you...

156
00:12:52,519 --> 00:12:54,159
will have no one by your side.

157
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:55,440
Try it if you don't believe me.

158
00:12:57,159 --> 00:12:59,320
Mr. Sheng, are you here to see me...

159
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,399
or make me angry?

160
00:13:00,639 --> 00:13:02,960
You are making me sicker.

161
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,320
Come on.

162
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,919
I'm not welcome anymore, am I?

163
00:13:08,159 --> 00:13:09,600
I'll leave then.

164
00:13:10,759 --> 00:13:11,960
Stand up straight.

165
00:13:12,519 --> 00:13:13,559
Attention.

166
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,759
Take a bow and apologize.

167
00:13:17,159 --> 00:13:19,480
Then I'll let this slide.

168
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,600
A bow is fine.

169
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,440
My deepest condolences to you.

170
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,039
I...

171
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,559
All right.

172
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:31,759
That's enough.

173
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:14,879
Three.

174
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,480
Go ahead.

175
00:14:17,799 --> 00:14:19,120
What? What card did you play?

176
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,200
Seven.

177
00:14:21,679 --> 00:14:22,720
K.

178
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,759
K? Here's two.

179
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,080
Two? I can't take the card.

180
00:14:27,879 --> 00:14:28,960
No.

181
00:14:30,159 --> 00:14:31,159
Another two.

182
00:14:31,279 --> 00:14:32,399
- What? - Two.

183
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:33,720
I can't take it.

184
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,039
No.

185
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,200
It's my turn.

186
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,840
- Hello. - Hello.

187
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:52,840
Is there a patient here named Hou Zhi Rong?

188
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,440
Yes.

189
00:14:56,279 --> 00:14:57,799
Please pass this to him for me.

190
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,120
He's over there.

191
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,519
I will tell him to pick it up.

192
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:02,679
No. Please give this to him for me.

193
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:04,519
What is this?

194
00:15:04,519 --> 00:15:05,519
It's homemade porridge.

195
00:15:06,519 --> 00:15:07,519
What should I tell him?

196
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,720
Just say it's from the little girl...

197
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,639
Just say it's some porridge made by the old man.

198
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,960
- Thank you. - Okay.

199
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,360
A pair of circles.

200
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:21,080
- A pair of twos. - Double.

201
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:24,720
Joker bomb!

202
00:15:25,399 --> 00:15:27,600
Mr. Hou, the old man brought you porridge.

203
00:15:27,799 --> 00:15:29,320
Old man? Who is it?

204
00:15:29,559 --> 00:15:30,559
It was that old man.

205
00:15:30,559 --> 00:15:31,600
Which old man?

206
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,159
It was that old man.

207
00:15:33,399 --> 00:15:35,320
All right, you should go.

208
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,440
Which old man?

209
00:15:36,639 --> 00:15:38,720
What old man? Who are you to question me?

210
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:39,759
It's just a friend of mine.

211
00:15:40,399 --> 00:15:42,240
Shi Yi, get me some porridge.

212
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,639
- All right. - Thank you.

213
00:15:43,639 --> 00:15:44,879
It's over.

214
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,639
You're doomed. You've lost.

215
00:15:47,759 --> 00:15:48,919
Where did this old man come from?

216
00:15:48,919 --> 00:15:50,000
Come here.

217
00:15:50,679 --> 00:15:51,679
Put it on.

218
00:15:52,399 --> 00:15:53,440
- Put it on. - I'll do it myself.

219
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:55,919
Shuffle the cards, Zhou Quan.

220
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,320
It's done.

221
00:16:03,639 --> 00:16:04,679
Hurry up.

222
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,080
Here, eat it while it's hot.

223
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,240
Okay.

224
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:19,080
It's delicious.

225
00:16:30,519 --> 00:16:31,799
The porridge is really good.

226
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,120
Thank you, little girl.

227
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,360
Old man.

228
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,960
Have some more then.

229
00:16:53,159 --> 00:16:54,200
What are you doing?

230
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,960
Who is it? Who is the old man?

231
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,759
- I'm so worried. - Why do you care?

232
00:16:57,759 --> 00:16:59,279
Let me have my privacy, okay?

233
00:16:59,279 --> 00:17:00,720
Just sit down and play the cards.

234
00:17:02,919 --> 00:17:04,680
What's wrong with you today?

235
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:05,680
You got yourself an old man.

236
00:17:09,170 --> 00:17:10,410
You naughty girl.

237
00:17:26,039 --> 00:17:27,440
I'm coming.

238
00:17:30,170 --> 00:17:31,359
- You're back. - My dad is right behind.

239
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:32,410
- All right. - I'll go put my stuff down.

240
00:17:32,410 --> 00:17:33,410
- Sure. - Ms. Zhang.

241
00:17:33,890 --> 00:17:34,890
Ms. Zhang.

242
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,170
Mr. Hao, you're finally discharged.

243
00:17:37,170 --> 00:17:38,759
- That's a relief. - Here, change your shoes.

244
00:17:38,759 --> 00:17:40,410
No, you should rest. I'll get it for you.

245
00:17:40,410 --> 00:17:43,000
- They're dirty. - It's okay. Get some rest.

246
00:17:43,119 --> 00:17:45,170
You should rest. Slowly.

247
00:17:47,039 --> 00:17:48,079
Ms. Zhang.

248
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,559
While I was in the hospital,

